data.title: Clover’s mum straps Hockey
data.meta_description: Former NSW premier Nick Greiner awoke a few painful scars (mercifully, not of the gastric-banding kind) for his former staffer and would-be treasurer Joe Hockey on Wednesday in Canberra.
data.text:
Former NSW premier Nick Greiner awoke a few painful scars (mercifully, not of the gastric-banding kind) for his former staffer and would-be treasurer Joe Hockey on Wednesday in Canberra.

Greiner was asked at the launch of Ian Hancock’s Nick Greiner: A Political Biography about his dealings with a crossbench during his time in charge of a hung NSW parliament. He said he took a different approach to former PM Julia Gillard. “I never talked to them ... I had other people talk to them," Greiner said.
